---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Support — Turn a Phrase"
  description="Need help? Found a bug? Send us a note."
  path="support"
>
  <div class="container legal">
    <span class="eyebrow">Support</span>
    <h1>How can we help?</h1>

    <p>
      Turn a Phrase is built by a small team — we read every message that
      comes in, and we usually reply within a couple of days.
    </p>

    <div class="card">
      <h2 style="margin-top: 0">Email us</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:help@turnaphrase.app" class="btn" style="text-decoration: none">
          help@turnaphrase.app
        </a>
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: 24px; color: var(--ink-muted); font-size: 0.95rem">
        When reporting a bug, please include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your device (e.g. <em>iPhone 14 Pro</em>, <em>Pixel 7</em>)</li>
        <li>Your iOS / Android version</li>
        <li>The app version (Settings → bottom, e.g. <em>v0.4.1</em>)</li>
        <li>What you were doing when it happened</li>
        <li>A screenshot if you have one</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Common questions</h2>

    <h3>How do I delete my account?</h3>
    <p>
      Inside the app: <strong>Settings → Account → Delete account</strong>. The deletion is
      immediate and removes everything we have on you. See the
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for details.
    </p>

    <h3>Can I export my progress?</h3>
    <p>
      Yes. <strong>Settings → Content → Export my data</strong> creates a JSON file
      with your full learning history and opens the share sheet so you can save it
      to Files / Drive / wherever.
    </p>

    <h3>Why don't I see the daily reminder?</h3>
    <p>
      Open Settings inside the app, scroll to <strong>Notifications</strong>, and
      toggle <strong>Daily reminder</strong> on. The first time you tap it, your
      device will ask for notification permission. If you previously denied it,
      you'll need to enable notifications for Turn a Phrase in your phone's
      system Settings as well.
    </p>

    <h3>Is there a web version?</h3>
    <p>
      Not yet. v1 is mobile-only — the spaced-repetition + streak loop works best
      with the daily push reminder, which isn't great in a browser context.
    </p>

    <h3>Where do the idioms come from?</h3>
    <p>
      The bulk of our 1,500+ idiom library is drawn from public-domain
      lexicographic sources (Wiktionary's English idioms category is the
      backbone), with each entry's origin story, examples, and quiz distractors
      generated by Claude (Anthropic's language model) and reviewed by us. The
      contested-etymology field means we're occasionally wrong — please tell us
      if you spot one.
    </p>

    <h3>Will there ever be ads or a paywall?</h3>
    <p>
      No ads, ever. No paywall in v1. If we ever introduce optional premium
      features, the core daily-learning loop will stay free.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
